    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 109.</note>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Read</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Davis</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-18">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 18, 1870</date>. (Received August
                        20.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cannot get gold; silver only can be bad. Business clogged and people indignant. I
                    strongly advise taking silver.</p>
                <p>Can I bank with Hottinguer, Barings’ correspondent here; unwilling to have
                    responsibility of funds at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>READ, <hi rend="italic">Paris.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
